> If it used {} as a temporary placeholder, we'd see args={}

As I understand we'd never see `{}` as a temporary placeholder. We concatenate string args when summing AIMessageChunks; there's no mechanism to revise earlier chunks as you'd need to do with a placeholder (let me know if I misunderstood that).

If a tool call has no args, when streaming you either stream an empty string or the string `"{}"` (Anthropic does the former, OpenAI and Gemini do the latter, for example). These correctly get parsed to an empty dict here: https://github.com/langchain-ai/langchain/blob/f08dfb6f4916c1eeb1743501958d2672896ef281/libs/core/langchain_core/messages/ai.py#L355
